<Base
  title="Google Workspace vs Microsoft 365 for Japan SMEs: Honest Comparison — MKUltraman"
  description="Google Workspace vs Microsoft 365 for Japan SMEs — pricing, Excel dominance in Japan, Teams vs Meet, local support, and which suite fits your business."
  article={true}
  pubDate={pubDate}
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="compare">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="compare-article">
        <header class="compare-header">
          <a href="/compare/" class="back-link">← All comparisons</a>
          <span class="compare-eyebrow">Comparison · Last verified {lastVerified}</span>
          <h1>Google Workspace vs Microsoft 365 for Japan SMEs</h1>
          <p class="compare-lead">
            Both productivity suites cost nearly the same and offer similar
            features. But Japan's business culture tilts heavily toward Excel
            and desktop Office apps. Here's the honest breakdown on pricing,
            Excel compatibility, and when each one fits your business.
          </p>
          <div class="compare-meta">
            <span>By <a href="/about/" rel="author">Matt Ketchum</a></span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>Tokyo</span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>~9 min read</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <aside class="tldr" aria-label="Verdict summary">
          <h2 class="tldr__heading">Verdict</h2>
          <div class="verdict">
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>Google Workspace wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>New businesses (greenfield, no legacy Microsoft files)</li>
                <li>Foreign-owned SMEs with international teams</li>
                <li>Startups and tech companies</li>
                <li>Teams that want cloud-first collaboration</li>
                <li>Businesses where Gmail is preferred over Outlook</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>Microsoft 365 wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Japan-domestic businesses with heavy Excel workflows</li>
                <li>Organizations that need Teams for enterprise compliance</li>
                <li>Parent company M365 ecosystem requirements</li>
                <li>Businesses that need desktop Office apps</li>
                <li>Document exchange with Japanese clients and partners</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="verdict__conclusion">
            Japan's business culture is deeply Excel-dependent — invoices, project plans,
            expense reports, client deliverables all arrive as .xlsx files. For any business
            that exchanges documents heavily with Japanese clients and partners,
            <strong>Microsoft 365's Excel advantage is real and material</strong>. Google
            Workspace is the right call for new or internationally-focused businesses where
            the team can set the collaboration norms.
          </p>
        </aside>

        <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
          <h2 class="toc__heading">On this page</h2>
          <ol class="toc__list">
            <li><a href="#at-a-glance">At a glance</a></li>
            <li><a href="#pricing">Pricing reality</a></li>
            <li><a href="#excel-problem">The Excel problem in Japan</a></li>
            <li><a href="#email">Email: Gmail vs Outlook</a></li>
            <li><a href="#collaboration">Collaboration and real-time editing</a></li>
            <li><a href="#japan-factors">Japan-specific factors</a></li>
            <li><a href="#decision-framework">Decision framework</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq">Frequently asked questions</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <section id="at-a-glance" class="compare-section">
          <h2>At a glance</h2>
          <div class="compare-table-wrap">
